long_desc.thetext: Setting the ColumnWidth failes for Columns > 0 failes. When setting the ColumnWidth an Error occurres in the ScrollBar: 009078 ERROR: qx.ui.core.ScrollBar(975): Modification of property "maximum" failed with exception: TypeError - this.getParent() has no properties
Could you please post a screenshot, the complete stack trace and a small example page that shows the error.
Created attachment 23 demo test for changing columnwidth of a tableColumnModel

To set the width via the table doesn't make any differences because setColumnWidth of table just call the setColumnWith method of its columnModel. Setting the Column 0 is successful but all Columns > 0 failes.
(In reply to comment #4) > When I first tried to set the column widths of the table I too got this error. > But what I found was that I was accessing the columns starting at 1, but the > columns are zero based. Also, I did not set the column width via > tableColumnModel I did it straight from the table: > > myTable = new qx.ui.table.Table(tableModel); > myTable.setColumnWidth(0,45); > myTable.setColumnWidth(1,145); > myTable.setColumnWidth(2,100); > > etc. >

Created attachment 25 Gif Animation of inspection the tablecolumns
At checking the columns of my table with the FireBug inspector, I found that strange behavior that the first column (0) has its own div tag and all others are included in one div tag. Perhaps this has something to do with this bug.

Bug is fixed in SVN.
The problem was that setting the value to a scroll bar didn't work, when a parent of the scrollbar wasn't in the ClientDocument. That's why setting the column width didn't work before the table was added to a parent.
Added the test to source/demo/test/Table_5.html

> At checking the columns of my table with the FireBug inspector, I found that > strange behavior that the first column (0) has its own div tag and all others > are included in one div tag. Perhaps this has something to do with this bug.
No. This is intentional. This is how the meta columns are realized. It's a feature, not a bug ;-)
